Manti-La Sal National Forest. F.S. road 027 west out of Wales, Utah until you encounter F.S. 157. Go South on F.S. 157 until you encounter a large saddle. To the East of the saddle you will find a large dead juniper that has has the upper portion cut off. Just a few steps East of the Juniper is a large rock that is being used for this site.

Up Big Cottonwood canyon. Entering Storm mountain campground headed toward the amphitheater. Following the trail past the amphitheater the hike gains elevation and makes a small loop until you are above the campground. On this ridge there are many sedimentary layered rocks with various lichens species living there.
